# Live execution visibility (mandatory)

## Portal SoT

- `src/content/execution-runtime.json` (canonical)
- `src/contracts/` — shared schemas
- API: `GET/PATCH /api/execution-runtime`
- UI: `/operations/live` (poll 8s)

## Cursor — NEVER silent during work

Every phase change and every 12s during long tasks:

```bash
npm run execution:phase -- --phase coding --task "..." --subsystem ... --reasoning "..." --confidence 0.85 --next "..." --progress "step"
npm run execution:heartbeat   # or: npm run execution:daemon
npm run execution:banner      # re-print [AION ACTIVE] block
npm run execution:waiting-review -- --pending 5
npm run execution:heal
npm run execution:stale-recover
npm run execution:finalize-live   # build + verify:routes + deploy:validate
```

Console format (script prints automatically):

```
[AION ACTIVE]
phase: coding
task: ...
next: validate build
```

## Phases (deterministic)

`idle | analyzing | planning | coding | validating | deploying | waiting_review | blocked | recovering | completed`

Also allowed: `reviewing | waiting_approval`

## After owner Apply

Resume with `execution:phase --phase coding` — **never ask "what next?"**

## Self-healing

On build/typecheck/deploy/route failure: `execution:heal` (retries deploy, escalates only if recovery confidence < 0.45).

## Feed

Phase transitions auto-append via `execution-runtime.mjs`. Milestones: `npm run feed:append`.

## Do NOT

- Fake heartbeat without work
- Stream raw chain-of-thought
- Push aion-driver to portal repo
